event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0827080600a022500069973ac0dfb88193ae36b69e61c1d9b3","logprobs":[],"output_index":0,"sequence_number":189,"text":"### Findings from Regional and Phenomena Searches\n\n**Regional Weather Differences**:\n- **Northern California**: More rainfall, cooler temperatures, lush forests.\n- **Southern California**: Warmer, drier, more sunshine.\n- **Coastal Areas**: Fog and moderated temperatures.\n- **Central Valley**: Hot summers, foggy winters, agricultural hub.\n- **Mountain Regions**: Heavy snowfall, cooler temperatures.\n- **Desert Regions**: Extreme heat, minimal rainfall.\n\n**Notable Weather Phenomena**:\n- **Droughts**: Frequent, affecting water and agriculture.\n- **Wildfires**: Increasing in frequency and intensity.\n- **Atmospheric Rivers**: Major precipitation source, can cause flooding.\n- **Santa Ana Winds**: Increase fire danger.\n- **El Niño/La Niña**: Impact precipitation and temperature patterns.\n\nNow, I'll create a document summarizing these findings."}

